{{ja-kanjitab|こい|yomi=k}}
{{IPAfont|⟨ko<sub>1</sub>pi<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/kʷopʷɨ/}} → {{IPAchar|/kofi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kowi/}} → {{IPAchar|/koi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=こい|-}}.

The {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||stem or continuative form}} of verb {{m|ja|恋う|tr=kou||to [[love]], [[yearn]]}}.

{{ja-noun|kyu=戀|こい|hhira=こひ}}

# [[love]], ''especially'' [[romantic]] love
#* {{RQ:Goshuishu|14|815; also ''{{w|Hyakunin Isshu}}'', poem 65}}
#*: {{ja-usex|恨みわびほさぬ袖だにあるものを'''恋'''に朽ちなむ名こそ惜しけれ|うらみ わび ほさぬ そで だに ある もの を '''こひ''' に くちなむ な こそ をしけれ|rom=urami wabi hosanu sode dani aru mono o '''koi''' ni kuchinan na koso oshikere|Anger and sorrow have made my never-dry sleeves a complete ruin―but still more hateful to me is '''love's''' ruin of my good name.<ref>{{cite-book|1991|Steven D. Carter|Traditional Japanese Poetry: An Anthology|edition=illustrated|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0-8047-2212-9|page=227}}</ref>|sort=こい}}
# [[longing]], [[yearning]]
#* {{RQ:Shuishu|11|622; also ''{{w|Ogura Hyakunin Isshu|Hyakunin Isshu}}'', poem 40}}
#*: {{ja-usex|しのぶれど色に出でにけりわが'''恋'''は物や思ふと人の問ふまで|しのぶれど いろ に いでにけり わが '''こひ''' は もの や おもふ と ひと の とふ まで|rom=shinoburedo iro ni idenikeri waga '''koi''' wa mono ya omou to hito no tou made|Even though I hide it, it shows all over my face, such is my '''longing''' so that people ask me "What ''are'' you thinking about?"<ref>{{cite-book|1996|Joshua S. Mostow |Pictures of the Heart: The Hyakunin Isshu in Word and Image|edition=illustrated|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|isbn=0-8248-1705-2|page=260}}</ref>|sort=こい}}

